Plain-language summary (the terms below are what actually apply): use JonDash for
free for your own personal, non-commercial purposes. Don't sell it, don't charge
for it, and don't hand out copies. You may build your own add-on modules — but if
you share an add-on with anyone else, you must publish it in your own public code
repository and let the author know via GitHub so it can be linked. This summary is
not legal advice.

1. Personal use. The copyright holder grants you a free, non-exclusive,
   non-transferable licence to download, install, run, and use JonDash for your own
   personal, non-commercial purposes.

2. No commercial use or sale. You may not sell, rent, lease, sublicense, or charge
   for JonDash or for access to it; use it to provide a paid or commercial service;
   or use it for any commercial purpose — without the prior written permission of
   the copyright holder.

3. No redistribution. You may not distribute, republish, or give copies of JonDash
   (in whole or in part, in source or compiled form) to anyone else. Point people to
   the official repository so they can obtain their own copy under this licence. A
   hosting platform's view / fork / clone / download features are permitted only so
   that you may read the source and obtain your own personal copy under this licence,
   in accordance with that platform's terms of service.

4. Add-on modules and modifications. You may create add-on modules and personal
   modifications of JonDash for your own personal use under sections 1–3. If you make
   an add-on module available to any other person, you must:
     (a) publish that add-on in your own public source-code repository; and
     (b) notify the copyright holder (Jonti Adcock) via GitHub — for example through
         the profile at https://github.com/jontiadcock — so that it can be linked or
         listed.
   You may not sell shared add-ons, and you may not distribute a shared add-on in
   closed-source form.

5. Reserved rights. All rights not expressly granted here are reserved by the
   copyright holder.

6. No warranty. THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND,
   EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY,
   FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, AND NONINFRINGEMENT. IN NO EVENT SHALL THE
   COPYRIGHT HOLDER BE LIABLE FOR ANY CLAIM, DAMAGES, OR OTHER LIABILITY, WHETHER IN
   AN ACTION OF CONTRACT, TORT, OR OTHERWISE, ARISING FROM, OUT OF, OR IN CONNECTION
   WITH THE SOFTWARE, ITS USE, OR ITS VIEWING.

7. Contact. For commercial licensing, or for any permission not granted above,
   contact the copyright holder via https://github.com/jontiadcock.
